status_message: This morning I ran across this story about the Army's 6888th all-female battalion in WWII. I found it inspiring, eye-opening. I hope you do too. A black woman growing up in the Jim Crow South could have turned angry and bitter. Instead she proudly forged her own future, sacrificing in the way that she was allowed, for the country that was still not treating her race equally. Do we appreciate these stories today? Do our children learn about the patriotism of the most oppressed people throughout our history? We must teach them.
link_name: Stories We Should Know: Patriotism Over Bitterness
